1. Node.js is designed to be a platform to run JavaScript application on the server side; Express.js is based on Node.js and is a framework that provides features for applications.

2. package.json contains data regarding your application, the most important piece being the list of dependencies it needs from npm when npm install is run.


1. The files are static in that they are not being created dynamically by the server side.

2. It no longer displays 'Hello, World'; this is because the message sent by app.js is overridden by the explicit request for the text file entered in the URL.   
